\b 1) Introduction\b0\par
\par
In Vector Drawing, you use "Objects".\par
An object is like a layer in other graphic tool, but it's composed by severals shapes.\par
Each object can have one or more shapes.\par
\par
\b 1.1) Object\par
\par
\b0 You can change some parameters of the selected objected (in object panel) : \par
- Name, x,y ,width, height, depth\par
\par
Shape tool :\par
- first you select the shape you want to add : shape, box, ellipse, line, curve, image, text\par
- than you draw it on the canvas\par
\par
You can add this shape on the current object, or create a new object.\par
\par
\i To create a new object, when creating a new shape, set the checkbox 'Create new objet', in object panel.\i0\par
\par
\b 1.2) Shapes\b0\par
\par
There are several type of shapes : \par
- box : square or rectangle \par
- ellipse : ellipse or circle \par
- line : right line\par
- curve : curved line\par
- image : an image (png, jpg)\par
- text : a text\par
- complex shape : it's a particular shape, composed by several curves attached and close. The complex shape are the more powerfull type.\par
\par
Each shapes has its own parameters : \par
- x, y, alpha, color, width, height, offset (x,y), depth\par
- style (filled, line, dash, dot), parameters for style : width, height, distance\par
- FX\par
\par
Fx are usefull to create special fx on the shape (border, shadow (internal, external)...\par
Fx parameters : \par
- Style (filled, line, dash, dot), width, height, distance, x,y,scale, alpha, color, activated\par
\par
\par
\i How to create a new shape (box, circle, line, complex shape...) ?\i0\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 To create a line or a curve,select the line or curve tool, then clic and move the mouse.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}to create a box or ellipse, select the tool, then clic and move the mouse.\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\par
How to add a shape, from the shape preset : \par
- select the shape you want in the combobox, panel shape\par
- clic on "add" button\par
\par
You can add new complex shape preset, they are in the folder : data\\shapes\\\par
\par
\par
\b 2) transformations\par
\b0\par
You can select, move, scale or rotate a shape (or several shapes if they are selected).\par
\par
\b 2.1) selection\b0\par
\par
Select severals shapes: use the shapelist or use th shift + clic on the shape to select it.\par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 To move,rotate,scale a shape, first  :  select the object which contain this Shape, then move the mouse \par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\par
\b 2.2) add points / delete points\b0\par
\par
Add points to a shape : work with shape, line or curve.\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl240\slmult1 To add point to the shape, curve or line, use 'addpoint' tool.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}To delete a point, use the "delete point tool" and clic on the point you want to delete\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\par
\b 2.3) transformations : move, rotate, scale\b0\par
\par
You can move, rotate or scale a shape with the tool "move, "rotate" or scale".\par
You can move one point with the "move" tool.\par
\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\b 3) Edition\b0\par
\par
- Copy/paste a shape : \par
With ctrl+C/Ctrl+V : you can copy a shape and past it.\par
\par
- delete the selected shape : you can use the "delete" key, or clic on the "-", in the shape panel\par
